The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 November is 103,968 (11,982.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 November, there were 4,623 new confirmed cases (532.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 November, there were 3,812 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 21% (811 extra cases).
